00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,639
Tatarn's Facebook is public.

60
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:32,519
It seems like he wants
to send someone a message.

61
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,600
That someone

62
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,559
could be Nut.

63
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,360
But there's not
a single photo of Nut here.

64
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,919
There's also no information
about Tatarn's whereabouts, job,

65
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:46,080
nor how to contact him.

66
00:09:55,039 --> 00:10:00,000
TATARN, OUR LIFE

67
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,200
That man seems familiar.

68
00:10:11,679 --> 00:10:13,399
Is it someone who knows Nut?

69
00:10:16,639 --> 00:10:18,360
He's not just someone he knows.

70
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:20,639
He's someone Nut loved.

71
00:10:27,519 --> 00:10:30,879
Why would you look at his pictures?

72
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:34,159
Don't worry about it.

73
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,919
He's the past.

74
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,279
Now, you're the only one for Nut, okay?

75
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,840
Are you and Nut in love?

76
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,399
Yes.

77
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:10,559
You got it right.

78
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:12,720
We are in love.

79
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,440
Tofu makes me happy.

80
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:20,440
He's the reason I can tolerate this house.

81
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:25,679
What are you trying to do
by asking him behind my back?

82
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,039
Are you driving him away again?

83
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,279
Are you doing the same thing again?

84
00:11:38,399 --> 00:11:39,399
Don't go anywhere,

85
00:11:39,879 --> 00:11:41,600
or I'll go with you.

86
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:45,600
If you can't accept it,
then I won't stay here.

87
00:11:46,799 --> 00:11:48,039
Where are you going?

88
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,279
You're my son.

89
00:11:52,159 --> 00:11:53,840
Your son is gay!

90
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:58,960
If you dream of a happy family
like you find in books,

91
00:11:59,759 --> 00:12:01,039
I can tell you now

92
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:03,559
that it will never come true

93
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,879
because I like men.

94
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,759
I can never marry a woman
and give you grandkids.

95
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,120
Calm down, Nut.

96
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,879
Are you hurt

97
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,080
to have me as a son?

98
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,480
It hurts me, too,

99
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:26,559
that you're my mom.

100
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,240
You can hate me all you want.

101
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,120
But I will never be who you want me to be.

102
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,120
Nut.

103
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,960
If you want me to stay,

104
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,159
I'll stay,

105
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,879
but I'll be myself.

106
00:12:51,039 --> 00:12:52,159
I'll love him like this.

107
00:12:58,039 --> 00:12:59,000
What are you doing?

108
00:13:09,159 --> 00:13:10,039
Nut.

109
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:21,200
Nut.

110
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,039
Nut.

111
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,159
Nut.

112
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,440
Let's talk.

113
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:38,000
You'll never understand
what I went through.

114
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,720
All you do is side with her.

115
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,960
I don't.

116
00:13:42,039 --> 00:13:43,600
I just didn't want you to do that.

117
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,440
Nut.

118
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,480
Nut!

119
00:14:06,799 --> 00:14:07,840
Song.

120
00:14:10,039 --> 00:14:10,879
Here.

121
00:14:16,519 --> 00:14:18,679
Why did you come all the way here?

122
00:14:20,799 --> 00:14:22,120
I had a fight with Tofu.

123
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:24,279
I don't want to see him.

124
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:25,960
What did he do?

125
00:14:28,639 --> 00:14:30,360
I'll change the question.

126
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,120
What did you do?

127
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:40,879
My mom knows I'm with Tofu.

128
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,799
What did she say?

129
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,720
I don't care

130
00:14:48,279 --> 00:14:49,559
if she yells at me.

131
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:52,519
I won't break up with him like last time.

132
00:14:55,159 --> 00:14:57,240
Are you saying
that you broke up with your ex

133
00:14:57,759 --> 00:14:59,039
because of your mom?

134
00:15:08,679 --> 00:15:10,279
What does Tofu have to do with it?

135
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,440
He doesn't understand me.

136
00:15:14,919 --> 00:15:18,279
I kissed him in front of Mom to spite her,

137
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:20,559
and he just pushed me away.

138
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,759
I wouldn't just push you away.

139
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,919
I would dropkick you.

140
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,360
Why are you acting like a child?

141
00:15:29,919 --> 00:15:33,440
Don't you ever consider his feelings?

142
00:15:34,519 --> 00:15:35,600
What about your mom's?

143
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,279
Fine.

144
00:15:42,039 --> 00:15:43,159
I know I was wrong,

145
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,279
but I wanted to hurt her

146
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,120
like she hurt me before.

147
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,840
All right.

148
00:16:01,639 --> 00:16:04,279
Hey, come. Let's have lunch.

149
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,919
Here. These are all Nut's favorites.

150
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,480
It has been a while.

151
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,559
Let's eat.

152
00:16:10,639 --> 00:16:11,919
He has a boyfriend now.

153
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,879
He has forgotten about his friends.

154
00:16:15,399 --> 00:16:16,840
Stop talking about him.

155
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,440
If I can't talk about him,
then you can leave.

156
00:16:20,519 --> 00:16:21,720
Go home. Get out.

157
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:25,879
Hey, you're always welcome here,

158
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:29,600
but I would be glad
if you were happier at home.

159
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,879
Who's here?

160
00:16:49,399 --> 00:16:51,679
How did you know Nut was here?

161
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,879
Lovers should know each other well,

162
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,399
just like how I know you.

163
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,519
You brought Tofu all the way here,

164
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:04,559
you can anticipate war.

165
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:19,160
Our weekend seems jolly today.

166
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:27,279
You guys must be hungry.

167
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:29,279
Let's dig in.

168
00:17:29,359 --> 00:17:30,400
-Come on.
-Okay.

169
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,599
Let's eat.

170
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,319
I remember that you like eggplant.

171
00:18:07,559 --> 00:18:09,559
-Nut.
-Get that for me.

172
00:18:13,519 --> 00:18:14,359
I want that piece.

173
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,359
-Nut.
-Give me some fried pork too.

174
00:18:51,359 --> 00:18:54,160
Do you want anything else?
I'll get it all for you now.

175
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,640
I don't.

176
00:18:56,359 --> 00:18:57,799
Just eat. Don't bother me.

177
00:18:59,559 --> 00:19:02,519
How can I eat when you're mad?

178
00:19:04,319 --> 00:19:06,920
Whose fault is it that I'm mad?

179
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,079
Hey.

180
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,759
Whoever's fault it is,

181
00:19:09,839 --> 00:19:13,240
let's clear it up after we eat.

182
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:15,519
It would be a shame to ruin lunch.

183
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,359
I don't know what you fought about,

184
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:27,720
but there aren't many chances for us
to eat together like this.

185
00:19:28,279 --> 00:19:30,359
So the time that we spend together

186
00:19:30,839 --> 00:19:32,599
should be a happy time.

187
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:35,720
The dining table is a war-free zone.

188
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,960
-We should enjoy the food.
-Right.

189
00:19:40,799 --> 00:19:42,640
-I'm sorry.
-Okay.

190
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,000
I'm sorry.

191
00:19:44,559 --> 00:19:46,319
All right. That's that.

192
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,240
Let's eat,

193
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:50,079
so we can cheer up with desserts.

194
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,839
Do you think you own the place?

195
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,559
What?

196
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:09,599
You almost destroyed my home

197
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:10,759
by bringing Tofu here.

198
00:20:10,839 --> 00:20:11,880
Just leave.

199
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,920
I won't.

200
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,880
-You won't?
-Right.

201
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,400
Your dad invited me to stay.

202
00:20:27,839 --> 00:20:30,720
Nut. Talk it out nicely, okay?

203
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,480
Thank you for lunch, Gen.

204
00:20:38,519 --> 00:20:40,079
Thank you, too, Song.

205
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,440
Right.

206
00:20:41,519 --> 00:20:43,559
Thank you for your meddling.

207
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,039
I'm so darn touched.

208
00:20:46,799 --> 00:20:48,319
Let me tell you about Gen.

209
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,960
-What are you doing, Nut?
-Don't worry.

210
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,880
Nut. What did you say?

211
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,079
You'll find out soon.

212
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:15,640
What did he say, Song?

213
00:21:36,519 --> 00:21:37,359
What is this?

214
00:21:39,079 --> 00:21:40,240
Can we turn it off?

215
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,279
Gosh, Nut.

216
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,160
Nut.

217
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:49,319
Ouch.

218
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:51,839
Nut.

219
00:22:04,279 --> 00:22:05,359
Tofu.

220
00:22:28,799 --> 00:22:30,559
If something is bothering you,

221
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:34,480
you can tell me.

222
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,519
You might feel better.

223
00:22:47,359 --> 00:22:48,359
I'm sorry

224
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,559
for what I did just now and at home.

225
00:22:54,319 --> 00:22:55,519
I'm not mad.

226
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:00,160
I know you probably feel bad too.

227
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,599
Don't you?

228
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,880
I know I was wrong,

229
00:23:10,559 --> 00:23:12,480
but Mom was wrong too.

230
00:23:15,079 --> 00:23:16,519
It may be hard to imagine,

231
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,640
but Mom and I used to be close.

232
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:21,720
But as I grew up,

233
00:23:22,519 --> 00:23:23,519
I found out

234
00:23:24,279 --> 00:23:26,359
that we were never really close.

235
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:37,680
-Mom.
-Yes?

236
00:23:37,759 --> 00:23:40,960
They say that Thailand
was never colonized.

237
00:23:41,039 --> 00:23:43,519
What about the two times we lost to Burma?

238
00:23:43,599 --> 00:23:44,960
Well…

239
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:50,279
we only count the Western Colonization
during the Rattanakosin period,

240
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:54,240
not during the Ayutthaya period,
since we weren't a country back then.

241
00:23:55,279 --> 00:23:58,000
What are the pros and cons

242
00:23:58,079 --> 00:24:00,319
of never being colonized?

243
00:24:04,279 --> 00:24:05,599
What are we talking about?

244
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,119
I have something for you.

245
00:24:15,559 --> 00:24:16,839
I'm hungry.

246
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:18,839
I'll cook you something.

247
00:24:49,079 --> 00:24:50,400
Isn't this pretty?

248
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:56,240
Nut. That's a girl's dress.
You can't wear that.

249
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:02,839
Why not? Can't boys wear it?

250
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,599
I like this dress.

251
00:25:07,119 --> 00:25:09,759
Pink is for girls.

252
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,759
What color is for boys, then?

253
00:25:13,839 --> 00:25:16,319
Why can't it be pink?

254
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:26,160
Haven't I told you
not to let him play with these?

255
00:25:40,559 --> 00:25:41,559
Sib.

256
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,559
-You shouldn't go so far--
-Shut it.

257
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:50,119
He's turning gay
because of your negligence.

258
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,880
-He's just a nice boy.
-Don't talk back to me.

259
00:25:54,359 --> 00:25:56,240
Boys have to be strong.

260
00:25:56,319 --> 00:25:58,480
What kind of mom are you?

261
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,079
Nut!

262
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:14,519
Honey!

263
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:17,359
Hey! Stop!

264
00:27:18,319 --> 00:27:21,400
Do you see
he's wearing heels like a queen?

265
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:24,039
Do you want to be one?

266
00:27:24,119 --> 00:27:25,759
Do you want to be gay?

267
00:27:25,839 --> 00:27:27,799
Don't you want to be a man?

268
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:29,640
Answer me!

269
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,079
What are you looking at?

270
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:44,440
What did I do wrong?

271
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:47,839
Why can't boys play with paper dolls?

272
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,240
Why can't we like pink?

273
00:27:50,799 --> 00:27:52,680
Why can't we wear heels?

274
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:55,920
