00:58:28,159 --> 00:58:29,559
I'm a bit jealous.

559
00:58:30,800 --> 00:58:32,639
But when it comes to your stories,

560
00:58:33,239 --> 00:58:34,480
I want to know everything.

561
00:58:36,559 --> 00:58:39,519
You're just thinking of him,

562
00:58:40,199 --> 00:58:41,679
but you aren't missing him.

563
00:58:47,239 --> 00:58:51,360
Finally, I got to know
how Nut ended up with Tatarn.

564
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:54,760
Their love seemed fine,

565
00:58:55,880 --> 00:58:56,840
but…

566
00:58:57,639 --> 00:59:02,400
what happened
between Nut, Tatarn, and Nut's mom?

567
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:06,519
Why have Nut and his mom
had a problem for so long?

568
00:59:11,159 --> 00:59:13,679
Right. What's your problem?

569
00:59:15,519 --> 00:59:17,800
My dad asked what the problem was.

570
00:59:17,880 --> 00:59:19,599
You've been watering for five minutes.

571
00:59:19,679 --> 00:59:21,519
My vegetables are probably dead.

572
00:59:22,559 --> 00:59:24,840
Gen cherishes that plot.

573
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:27,199
It will rot if you water it too much.

574
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:28,400
Gen will yell at you.

575
00:59:28,480 --> 00:59:30,360
I don't cherish it.

576
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:32,480
My mistake.

577
00:59:32,960 --> 00:59:34,079
You used to cherish it.

578
00:59:34,880 --> 00:59:36,599
That plot was for his ex.

579
00:59:36,679 --> 00:59:37,960
Dad! Don't.

580
00:59:38,760 --> 00:59:39,760
Is that true?

581
00:59:43,800 --> 00:59:45,679
Yes. Well…

582
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:48,159
my ex wouldn't eat vegetables,

583
00:59:48,239 --> 00:59:50,239
so I tried to get him to eat those.

584
00:59:51,480 --> 00:59:52,800
He would only eat those

585
00:59:52,880 --> 00:59:54,079
if I planted them.

586
00:59:56,280 --> 00:59:58,079
That kid liked cabbage,

587
00:59:58,159 --> 01:00:00,280
so he paid special attention to those.

588
01:00:00,360 --> 01:00:01,800
Dad! Again?

589
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:06,199
I guess they're useless now
since you broke up.

590
01:00:06,920 --> 01:00:08,960
Can't I plant them for myself?

591
01:00:12,079 --> 01:00:13,559
I like ivy gourd leaves, though.

592
01:00:16,440 --> 01:00:17,360
Listen.

593
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:19,199
When you leave my house,

594
01:00:19,280 --> 01:00:21,199
turn left and you'll find a market.

595
01:00:21,280 --> 01:00:23,800
Buy as many as you like.

596
01:00:25,800 --> 01:00:27,440
Come on, mister.

597
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:29,760
I want you to plant those for me.

598
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:31,239
Just like this.

599
01:00:31,719 --> 01:00:33,119
Please.

600
01:00:33,639 --> 01:00:35,599
-Just a few.
-Why should I?

601
01:00:38,760 --> 01:00:39,960
Plant them yourself.

602
01:00:41,360 --> 01:00:42,480
I have the seeds.

603
01:00:43,239 --> 01:00:45,559
Really? Where?

604
01:00:45,639 --> 01:00:46,800
Over there.

605
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:50,199
I got them for free.

606
01:00:51,360 --> 01:00:53,679
Are my vegetables just a giveaway?

607
01:00:54,480 --> 01:00:56,719
Are you going to plant them or not?

608
01:00:59,480 --> 01:01:01,800
Of course, I am.

609
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:05,280
Hey.

610
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:11,880
Mr. Sitha, cool it.

611
01:01:11,960 --> 01:01:13,559
Well, yes.

612
01:01:13,639 --> 01:01:15,719
Yes. Okay.

613
01:02:20,800 --> 01:02:23,440
Wait. What's that?

614
01:02:23,519 --> 01:02:25,119
What's that?

615
01:02:26,800 --> 01:02:28,559
Meow.

616
01:02:30,039 --> 01:02:32,960
-Meow?
-Hey!

617
01:02:33,039 --> 01:02:35,360
What? Don't.

618
01:02:35,920 --> 01:02:37,800
I know why you like ivy gourd leaves.

619
01:02:37,880 --> 01:02:39,320
Why so?

620
01:02:39,840 --> 01:02:40,880
They're creepers.

621
01:02:40,960 --> 01:02:41,800
Hey.

622
01:02:41,880 --> 01:02:44,639
There. Take that.

623
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:46,400
Come here, Song.

624
01:02:46,480 --> 01:02:47,840
Stop.

625
01:02:55,519 --> 01:02:56,760
I'll wash it for you.

626
01:02:57,760 --> 01:03:00,440
Come on. Stop pestering me.

627
01:03:00,519 --> 01:03:01,679
I'm tired of yelling.

628
01:03:06,039 --> 01:03:07,559
I'm not fooling around anymore.

629
01:03:09,760 --> 01:03:12,239
Let me ask something serious.

630
01:03:15,719 --> 01:03:17,159
Do you not like younger guys?

631
01:03:22,000 --> 01:03:23,400
What are you saying?

632
01:03:24,639 --> 01:03:27,480
Earlier, Nut told me…

633
01:03:28,559 --> 01:03:31,360
Gen won't like you.
He doesn't like younger guys.

634
01:03:32,880 --> 01:03:34,039
Is it because of your ex?

635
01:03:36,880 --> 01:03:37,880
Earlier,

636
01:03:37,960 --> 01:03:39,440
your father said you went out

637
01:03:39,519 --> 01:03:40,760
with someone younger.

638
01:03:45,599 --> 01:03:49,639
Did your ex-boyfriend traumatize you
from dating a younger man?

639
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:54,639
Not all younger men are the same.

640
01:03:54,719 --> 01:03:55,960
Don't generalize us.

641
01:03:58,039 --> 01:04:00,280
The difference in our age
was only a few years,

642
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:02,039
yet my ex and I broke up.

643
01:04:03,199 --> 01:04:05,280
Our age gap is nine years.

644
01:04:06,480 --> 01:04:08,599
What if you meet someone better
in the future?

645
01:04:09,880 --> 01:04:11,360
What if you become famous?

646
01:04:12,519 --> 01:04:14,119
Your life has a long way to go.

647
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:18,559
That time hasn't come yet.

648
01:04:19,159 --> 01:04:20,440
Why would you worry?

649
01:04:24,800 --> 01:04:27,880
Do you think I'll turn out like them?

650
01:04:31,119 --> 01:04:32,960
Don't you have confidence in me

651
01:04:35,559 --> 01:04:37,800
when I'm with you at all?

652
01:04:46,320 --> 01:04:47,239
I…

653
01:04:49,639 --> 01:04:50,800
I don't want to risk it.

654
01:04:57,320 --> 01:04:58,760
Hey, Gen.

655
01:05:11,760 --> 01:05:12,960
Drink some water.

656
01:05:13,039 --> 01:05:14,000
Thank you.

657
01:05:18,239 --> 01:05:19,199
It's a little tough.

658
01:05:20,159 --> 01:05:21,840
Gen is a stubborn kid.

659
01:05:24,639 --> 01:05:27,440
I'm very serious about him.

660
01:05:28,920 --> 01:05:30,800
I don't know what else to do.

661
01:05:34,400 --> 01:05:36,920
Kanya and I were the same.

662
01:05:38,639 --> 01:05:40,519
When I pursued her,

663
01:05:40,599 --> 01:05:42,840
she was hard to get like Gen.

664
01:05:44,079 --> 01:05:48,400
When older women marry younger men,

665
01:05:48,480 --> 01:05:50,320
they worry about a million things.

666
01:05:51,320 --> 01:05:53,840
People would say
she's going out with her brother,

667
01:05:53,920 --> 01:05:56,079
or that she's my mom.

668
01:05:59,519 --> 01:06:01,519
What did you do, then?

669
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:03,760
I just kept going?

670
01:06:05,119 --> 01:06:06,639
You just kept going?

671
01:06:08,320 --> 01:06:09,559
What else could I do?

672
01:06:10,960 --> 01:06:12,800
If you really like him,

673
01:06:12,880 --> 01:06:14,719
then show him that.

674
01:06:14,800 --> 01:06:15,639
Just do it.

675
01:06:16,800 --> 01:06:18,159
It won't be a waste.

676
01:06:20,719 --> 01:06:23,480
As Gen's father

677
01:06:23,960 --> 01:06:25,599
who raised him with my own hands,

678
01:06:26,559 --> 01:06:29,559
his life has always been a breeze.

679
01:06:30,119 --> 01:06:31,960
He got to study what he wanted.

680
01:06:32,760 --> 01:06:34,119
He has a good job.

681
01:06:34,840 --> 01:06:37,039
Nobody minds who he is.

682
01:06:37,119 --> 01:06:40,800
Kanya and I have always understood
and supported him,

683
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:44,599
so he wants some things to be difficult.

684
01:06:46,199 --> 01:06:47,719
Love, for instance.

685
01:06:49,800 --> 01:06:52,039
I have to try harder, do I?

686
01:06:54,599 --> 01:06:56,119
Do your best, if you can.

687
01:06:57,360 --> 01:06:59,840
If you want some help, tell me.

688
01:07:01,760 --> 01:07:04,239
I'll understand if you want to give up.

689
01:07:04,920 --> 01:07:07,199
My son is high maintenance.

690
01:07:11,079 --> 01:07:12,280
Thank you.

691
01:07:18,519 --> 01:07:19,440
Cheer up.

692
01:07:28,760 --> 01:07:30,360
Have you two eaten?

693
01:07:48,199 --> 01:07:50,400
I'm sorry for keeping it from you.

694
01:07:52,039 --> 01:07:54,639
I didn't want to do that.

695
01:07:55,119 --> 01:07:57,880
I was just afraid you wouldn't like it,

696
01:07:59,519 --> 01:08:01,320
and that it would affect your health.

697
01:08:02,440 --> 01:08:05,039
I didn't want it to bother you.

698
01:08:10,679 --> 01:08:11,960
I'm sorry.

699
01:08:18,840 --> 01:08:20,199
What are you doing?

700
01:08:20,760 --> 01:08:22,119
I'm working.

701
01:08:23,479 --> 01:08:24,439
A change of scenery.

702
01:08:26,279 --> 01:08:28,600
I'm writing a boys' love screenplay.

703
01:08:29,279 --> 01:08:32,399
I get inspired with you around.

704
01:08:36,119 --> 01:08:39,760
I'll try not to make loud noises,
so you can focus on work.

705
01:08:42,560 --> 01:08:43,399
You want to know

706
01:08:44,760 --> 01:08:46,279
what I'm writing about?

707
01:08:49,800 --> 01:08:52,520
If you want to tell me, I'll listen.

708
01:08:54,159 --> 01:08:57,640
I'm writing about a boy's love.

709
01:08:59,439 --> 01:09:01,640
Despite being a high school love,

710
01:09:02,279 --> 01:09:04,279
it's not as jolly as a fantasy world.

711
01:09:05,159 --> 01:09:08,239
I won't write about
such an idealistic world.

712
01:09:10,079 --> 01:09:11,359
In reality,

713
01:09:12,079 --> 01:09:13,720
it's hard for men to be in love.

714
01:09:14,920 --> 01:09:17,199
Family, friends,

715
01:09:17,760 --> 01:09:19,760
or people next door don't accept it.

716
01:09:21,960 --> 01:09:23,359
That's just reality.

717
01:09:30,439 --> 01:09:33,640
Oh. It's time for Keunchai's dinner.

718
01:09:36,399 --> 01:09:38,399
He's probably starving.

719
01:09:38,479 --> 01:09:39,760
Then,

720
01:09:40,520 --> 01:09:42,119
I won't bother you anymore.

721
01:09:42,199 --> 01:09:43,600
Work hard.

722
01:09:45,439 --> 01:09:48,000
Come on, Keunchai. Let's eat.

723
01:09:48,079 --> 01:09:49,479
Come on.

724
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:51,720
Let's eat.

725
01:10:01,520 --> 01:10:03,279
What are you trying to do?

726
01:10:06,520 --> 01:10:07,800
Aren't you curious to see

727
01:10:08,319 --> 01:10:09,840
what will happen if Mom sees us?

728
01:10:15,520 --> 01:10:16,640
Let me help.

729
01:10:19,039 --> 01:10:19,960
Tofu.

730
01:10:21,600 --> 01:10:22,720
I want coffee.

731
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:25,359
Wait a second. I'm helping your mom.

732
01:10:26,039 --> 01:10:27,479
I want it now.

733
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:30,840
You should make him coffee.

734
01:10:47,920 --> 01:10:49,279
You're so slow.

735
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:52,680
Let me see it.

736
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:55,960
What are you doing?

737
01:11:01,760 --> 01:11:04,119
I want your attention. Can't I do this?

738
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:11,960
You usually know how to make coffee.

739
01:11:18,680 --> 01:11:20,119
Today, I forgot.

740
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:11,960
In case you're hungry.

741
01:12:14,119 --> 01:12:15,279
Thank you,

742
01:12:16,359 --> 01:12:17,319
but I'm not.

743
01:12:23,399 --> 01:12:24,239
Tofu.

744
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:28,279
Feed me. My hands are busy.

745
01:12:49,039 --> 01:12:49,880
Thanks.

746
01:13:10,279 --> 01:13:15,800
SCENE 36. BOOKSTORE. KAWEE, TONNAM.
KAWEE IS LOOKING AT BOOKS ON THE SHELF.

747
01:13:17,960 --> 01:13:24,279
KAWEE IS LOOKING
AT THE FRONT OF THE BOOKSTORE.

748
01:13:31,680 --> 01:13:33,439
I'll take it off for you.

749
01:13:36,720 --> 01:13:38,159
You can go.

750
01:13:49,119 --> 01:13:52,560
Since you're so inspired, any progress?

751
01:13:57,479 --> 01:13:58,520
Quite a lot.

752
01:13:59,479 --> 01:14:00,720
Perfect timing.

753
01:14:02,399 --> 01:14:03,359
Do a scene with me.

754
01:14:05,399 --> 01:14:06,520
What scene?

755
01:14:06,600 --> 01:14:07,640
You've only got that.

756
01:14:08,279 --> 01:14:10,520
Just do what I say.

757
01:14:11,079 --> 01:14:13,359
Stay still. I'll do the work.

758
01:14:15,640 --> 01:14:17,039
Let's do a romantic scene.

759
01:14:17,600 --> 01:14:19,439
Like this, Tofu.

760
01:14:20,119 --> 01:14:21,159
What are you doing?

761
01:14:21,239 --> 01:14:22,319
Come on.

762
01:14:23,600 --> 01:14:24,560
Nut.

763
01:14:28,520 --> 01:14:29,479
Nut!

764
01:14:33,560 --> 01:14:34,960
Let's talk.

765
01:14:41,760 --> 01:14:42,840
What's wrong with you?

766
01:14:44,880 --> 01:14:46,520
Why did you do that?

767
01:14:47,640 --> 01:14:50,239
You couldn't write a single scene anyway.

768
01:14:50,319 --> 01:14:52,039
That's my problem.

769
01:14:53,239 --> 01:14:56,399
It's not just your problem.
We live together.

770
01:14:59,920 --> 01:15:02,560
Are you saying that if you're not happy,

771
01:15:03,159 --> 01:15:05,199
no one else is allowed to be happy?

772
01:15:05,279 --> 01:15:06,239
That's not right.

773
01:15:06,319 --> 01:15:07,560
Tofu.

774
01:15:08,199 --> 01:15:09,119
You saw it.

775
01:15:09,640 --> 01:15:12,880
I went that far, but Mom still ignored me.

776
01:15:12,960 --> 01:15:15,840
The more she ignores me,
the more invisible I feel.

777
01:15:17,319 --> 01:15:20,560
Nut, it's not your fault
for being who you are,

778
01:15:21,119 --> 01:15:22,479
but it's not hers either.

779
01:15:23,439 --> 01:15:26,760
Your mom is just trying
to keep everyone in the household happy.

780
01:15:26,840 --> 01:15:28,239
It's fake happiness.

781
01:15:28,880 --> 01:15:30,439
She keeps fooling herself.

782
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:32,680
She has never really known me.

783
01:15:33,199 --> 01:15:35,199
How can we love each other

784
01:15:36,039 --> 01:15:37,520
when we barely know each other?

785
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:39,840
What do you want, then?

786
01:15:40,319 --> 01:15:43,800
If she knows the real you, she'll be hurt.

787
01:15:43,880 --> 01:15:46,840
When she's hurt, you're hurt.

788
01:15:47,319 --> 01:15:50,439
It's a circle of pain. When will it end?

789
01:15:53,000 --> 01:15:54,920
Why don't you try talking about it?

790
01:16:02,720 --> 01:16:05,359
I'm sorry.

791
01:16:05,439 --> 01:16:07,159
I didn't mean to eavesdrop.

792
01:16:07,239 --> 01:16:09,880
I just happened to hear it
while passing by.

793
01:16:09,960 --> 01:16:11,760
I'm really sorry.

794
01:16:12,479 --> 01:16:14,039
What are you fighting about?

795
01:16:22,920 --> 01:16:24,680
-I'm here.
-You're here.

796
01:16:24,760 --> 01:16:26,439
What took you so long?

797
01:16:26,520 --> 01:16:29,239
Gosh. Oh, take a seat.

798
01:16:30,439 --> 01:16:31,279
Well…

799
01:16:33,840 --> 01:16:35,159
Tofu.

800
01:16:35,239 --> 01:16:37,239
You don't look so good.

801
01:16:37,319 --> 01:16:38,720
Is there a problem at home?

802
01:16:40,399 --> 01:16:42,520
Nut and his mom are fighting.

803
01:16:43,720 --> 01:16:45,479
I don't know how to help.

804
01:16:46,479 --> 01:16:48,279
It's a tough job.

805
01:16:48,359 --> 01:16:50,000
Ever since I moved here,

806
01:16:50,079 --> 01:16:52,359
Na and Nut are always arguing.

807
01:16:52,439 --> 01:16:55,239
It's not that hard, Nhong.

808
01:16:55,840 --> 01:16:58,119
Of course, there's something we can do.

809
01:16:58,800 --> 01:16:59,720
Listen.

810
01:17:00,199 --> 01:17:04,079
Na and Nut are mother and son.

811
01:17:04,159 --> 01:17:07,119
Of course, they have some issues.
It's called a generation gap.

812
01:17:08,760 --> 01:17:10,359
Generation gap?

813
01:17:10,439 --> 01:17:11,359
Right.

814
01:17:11,920 --> 01:17:14,119
Nut grew up in an open world

815
01:17:14,199 --> 01:17:15,680
with freedom

816
01:17:15,760 --> 01:17:17,840
and all sorts of information.

817
01:17:18,399 --> 01:17:22,319
Whatever he does or asks, he needs facts.

818
01:17:22,399 --> 01:17:25,439
On the other hand,
Na is framed within her society.

819
01:17:25,520 --> 01:17:26,760
She's from my generation.

820
01:17:27,520 --> 01:17:29,880
She needs to be meticulous
in everything she does.

821
01:17:29,960 --> 01:17:31,680
That's her quality.

822
01:17:31,760 --> 01:17:34,039
She was taught that way
since she was born.

823
01:17:35,359 --> 01:17:37,880
They're from different generations.

824
01:17:37,960 --> 01:17:39,439
They both have expectations.

825
01:17:39,520 --> 01:17:41,680
Mother expects her son
to be a certain way.

826
01:17:41,760 --> 01:17:44,199
The son expects his mother
to be a certain way.

827
01:17:44,279 --> 01:17:47,640
The expectations
aren't met on either side,

828
01:17:47,720 --> 01:17:51,039
so they hurt each other
without realizing it.

829
01:17:56,319 --> 01:17:59,880
Wherever there's a gap,
you need to pay special attention.

830
01:17:59,960 --> 01:18:03,359
It can be dangerous
if the gap is too wide.

831
01:18:05,399 --> 01:18:07,199
How do we reduce the gap?

832
01:18:08,720 --> 01:18:09,560
Hey.

833
01:18:09,640 --> 01:18:11,920
The gap can be filled

834
01:18:12,000 --> 01:18:13,520
with family ties.

835
01:18:13,600 --> 01:18:16,000
If Nut and Na love each other,

836
01:18:16,079 --> 01:18:17,640
they should talk it out

837
01:18:17,720 --> 01:18:19,159
and maintain the ties.

838
01:18:19,239 --> 01:18:21,720
It will be fine
as long as they communicate.

839
01:18:27,439 --> 01:18:29,720
Because Mrs. Na and Nut won't communicate.

840
01:18:30,840 --> 01:18:34,279
she does things
without asking what Nut wants,

841
01:18:34,359 --> 01:18:36,520
as she thinks those are her duties

842
01:18:37,079 --> 01:18:38,119
as a mother.

843
01:18:39,960 --> 01:18:41,960
Nut also has demands from his mom.

844
01:18:42,479 --> 01:18:43,960
He always acts sarcastically,

845
01:18:44,560 --> 01:18:46,800
but he doesn't tell her what he wants.

846
01:18:50,199 --> 01:18:52,960
The gap between mother and child
should be narrow,

847
01:18:53,640 --> 01:18:55,319
but it keeps widening.

848
01:18:56,840 --> 01:18:58,520
I don't want it to be like this.

849
01:18:59,880 --> 01:19:01,439
Is there a way I can help them?

850
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:23,560
I'm sorry.

851
01:19:27,920 --> 01:19:28,840
Okay.

852
01:19:31,119 --> 01:19:33,039
It's not all your fault.

853
01:19:34,319 --> 01:19:36,680
I don't know how hard it is to be you,

854
01:19:38,079 --> 01:19:40,520
but it's not easy being your mom either.

855
01:19:43,479 --> 01:19:45,800
You might have faced
many things in your life,

856
01:19:47,960 --> 01:19:49,439
but your mom has too.

857
01:19:52,760 --> 01:19:55,159
I want you to think about her feelings.

858
01:20:00,159 --> 01:20:01,640
Thanks for reminding me.

859
01:20:03,039 --> 01:20:04,880
I'll try to be a better person.

860
01:20:07,880 --> 01:20:10,319
You're not that bad.

861
01:20:11,560 --> 01:20:13,159
Try to be positive.

862
01:20:14,880 --> 01:20:18,319
I think there are a lot more good things
in your life.

863
01:20:20,279 --> 01:20:23,399
You're the good thing in my life.

864
01:20:26,439 --> 01:20:27,680
It's not just me.

865
01:20:28,960 --> 01:20:30,560
Think harder.

866
01:20:35,119 --> 01:20:36,520
I told you.

867
01:20:37,159 --> 01:20:38,720
I won't talk about him anymore.

868
01:20:40,840 --> 01:20:42,119
It's okay.

869
01:20:42,840 --> 01:20:44,920
I want to know everything about you.

870
01:20:47,359 --> 01:20:49,399
I don't want you to act fine,

871
01:20:50,319 --> 01:20:52,079
when you're actually not.

872
01:20:56,640 --> 01:20:58,960
As long as you're not hurt
when you talk about it,

873
01:21:00,800 --> 01:21:02,199
I'll be fine.

874
01:21:08,960 --> 01:21:10,079
Continue.

875
01:21:11,520 --> 01:21:14,359
After you agreed to go out with Tatarn,

876
01:21:15,239 --> 01:21:16,800
how happy were you?

877
01:21:18,960 --> 01:21:20,600
It wasn't just happiness.

878
01:21:25,359 --> 01:21:26,560
The world at home

879
01:21:28,079 --> 01:21:29,960
and the world when I was with him

880
01:21:30,960 --> 01:21:32,199
were drastically different.

881
01:21:48,840 --> 01:21:49,720
Nut.

882
01:21:50,319 --> 01:21:53,039
Don't spend too much time on activities.

883
01:21:53,720 --> 01:21:55,560
Your dad is worried about your grades.

884
01:21:59,600 --> 01:22:01,079
And regarding that other matter,

885
01:22:01,159 --> 01:22:02,239
you should behave.

886
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:06,720
I won't stand it if you disobey me.

887
01:22:10,039 --> 01:22:11,239
Let's eat.

888
01:22:11,319 --> 01:22:12,439
I already ate.

889
01:22:25,199 --> 01:22:28,840
My parents act like I don't fit in

890
01:22:28,920 --> 01:22:31,760
and that it's embarrassing.

891
01:22:45,119 --> 01:22:46,079
Hey, Nut.

892
01:22:51,600 --> 01:22:52,840
I wrote it.

893
01:23:07,640 --> 01:23:08,560
How is it?

894
01:23:10,520 --> 01:23:11,760
It's great.

895
01:23:15,319 --> 01:23:16,960
-Really?
-Yes.

896
01:23:23,279 --> 01:23:25,560
You could become a writer.

897
01:23:28,319 --> 01:23:29,479
But Tarn

898
01:23:30,880 --> 01:23:33,640
made me feel like
I had discovered another world.

899
01:23:35,560 --> 01:23:36,840
He made me feel like

900
01:23:38,119 --> 01:23:40,279
I wasn't the only odd one out anymore.

901
01:25:46,560 --> 01:25:48,520
Having a rough guy like him around,

902
01:25:49,560 --> 01:25:52,399
who dared to do things
that wouldn't hurt anyone,

903
01:25:52,960 --> 01:25:56,239
got me to open my mind
and I started to feel free.

904
01:26:18,039 --> 01:26:19,000
Wait.

905
01:26:21,600 --> 01:26:22,680
Nut!

906
01:26:32,359 --> 01:26:33,640
Happy birthday, Nut.

907
01:26:36,119 --> 01:26:38,000
I didn't think I would get one this year.

908
01:26:39,199 --> 01:26:40,680
I wouldn't forget your birthday.

909
01:26:40,760 --> 01:26:43,000
I added jelly for you since you like it.

910
01:26:47,319 --> 01:26:48,479
Thank you.

911
01:26:49,560 --> 01:26:50,399
Try it.

912
01:27:03,279 --> 01:27:04,119
Is it good?

913
01:27:05,920 --> 01:27:06,960
Feed me.

914
01:27:09,079 --> 01:27:11,720
Okay. You can have a big bite.

915
01:27:11,800 --> 01:27:12,840
Is it too big?

916
01:27:13,960 --> 01:27:14,840
Is it too big?

917
01:27:16,600 --> 01:27:17,960
Here you go.

918
01:27:18,920 --> 01:27:20,039
Oh, wow.

919
01:28:16,960 --> 01:28:18,039
Your lips are sweet

920
01:28:19,399 --> 01:28:20,680
and soft like jelly.

921
01:28:37,960 --> 01:28:42,039
What happened to you in the past
made you lose faith in love,

922
01:28:42,119 --> 01:28:43,199
NEXT EPISODE

923
01:28:43,279 --> 01:28:46,680
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

924
01:28:46,760 --> 01:28:49,720
The reason you blow up at your mom…

925
01:28:52,840 --> 01:28:55,439
is to resist the feeling of love.

926
01:28:56,399 --> 01:28:58,640
But now that you've acknowledged
what happened,

927
01:29:00,079 --> 01:29:02,760
you feel better, don't you?

928
01:29:04,520 --> 01:29:06,159
You get irritable with your mom,

929
01:29:07,000 --> 01:29:08,560
but you're not really angry.

930
01:29:09,239 --> 01:29:11,359
You just…

931
01:29:12,359 --> 01:29:13,600
hold a grudge.

932
01:29:14,159 --> 01:29:15,520
You're such a know-it-all.

933
01:29:16,800 --> 01:29:18,159
Mom.

934
01:29:18,239 --> 01:29:19,920
-Mom!
-Mrs. Na.

